<root type="ability" class="self">

  <name>Exploding corpse</name>
  <description>
Although a lot of mages despise this spell, because of it&apos;s close relationship to necromancy, it&apos;s very useful in some situations - corpses of recently killed monsters explode, damaging nearby enemies. The longer the player hold&apos;s the spell key, the more corpses explode.  

Bonus for this spell depends:
  xxxxx on choleric rune
  xxxxx on melancholice rune
  xxxxx on sanguine rune
  xxxxx on phlegmatic rune  
  </description>
  <icon>data/abilities/weapons/exploding-corpse-0.png</icon>
  <unavailable-icon>data/abilities/weapons/exploding-corpse-1.png</unavailable-icon>

  <!-- power = 2x cho, 2x mel, 2x san, 2x phl -->
  <power calc="0.2 * dot(2, choleric, 2, melancholic, 2, sanguine, 2, phlegmatic)"/>
  
  <effect type="recastable" >
    <recast value="0.2" />
    <time value="5.0" />
    <effect type="retarget">
      <target-chooser>
        <filter value="hostiles"/>
        <range calc="7.0"/>
        <angle value="110.0"/>
        <aim-at-ground value="0" />
        <dead-bodies value="1"/>
      </target-chooser>
      <effect type="list">
        <effect type="sound">
          <name value="data/sounds/Lugaro/firestart.ogg" />
        </effect>
        <effect type="graphical-effect">
          <name value="bullet-explosion" />
          <time value="1.0" />
        </effect>
        <effect type="graphical-effect">
          <name value="smallfireball" />
          <time value="0.1" />
        </effect>
        <effect type="annihilate"/>
        <effect type="area">
          <area calc="1.3" />
          <filter value="hostiles,obstacle" />
          <effect type="list">
            <effect type="damage">
              <damage-type value="fire"/>
              <amount calc="19.0 * (1 + power)" />
            </effect>
            <effect type="knockback">
              <amount calc="2.0"/>
            </effect>
          </effect>
        </effect>
      </effect>
    </effect>
  </effect>

  <cast-time-effect type="modify">
    <aspect value="speed" />
    <amount value="0.2" />
  </cast-time-effect>

  <delay-effect type="modify">
    <aspect value="speed" />
    <amount value="0.1" />
  </delay-effect>

  <manacost calc="2.0" />
  <casttime calc="0.09" />
  <delay calc="0.05" />
  <cooldown value="0.0" />

  <focus-mana-cost calc="14.0 * (1 + 0.66 * power)" />
  <focus-max-duration value="5.0" />
</root>
